        "id": 1076138
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-04T19:14:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "But the environment in the child (child in this case \u003d\u003d the /bin/sh -c execution) will get its environment replaced in the call to execve(), right? So why does the environment in the parent matter? The shell invocation will see a single env var which will be TEST_VAR, no matter how you call the unit test binary... am I missing something here?",
      "parentUuid": "89fd47d5_6078398d",
      "revId": "08e8c229b495d3413ca41a02b345bf19cc151064",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
