    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "53966a59_6f75daf8",
        "filename": "libminijail_unittest.cc",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 344,
      "author": {
        "id": 1040868
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-04T19:37:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the default POSIX exec behavior is to inherit the parent\u0027s environment.  if the minijail code is buggy and doesn\u0027t actually replace the env, then the sh child execution will end up displaying the parent.\n\nso lets say you comment out this line in libminijail.c:\n\n //child_env \u003d config-\u003eenvp;\n\nthen run the unittests:\n\n TEST_VAR\u003dtest make check\n\nthis test will pass when it should have failed.\n\nyou prob should extend the test to also set a var in the parent and make sure it isn\u0027t set in the child.  i.e. you\u0027re verifying that not only was the env you specified passed through, but it fully replaced the env and didn\u0027t just augment it.\n\n // Parent.\n setenv(\"TEST_PARENT\", \"test\", 1);\n ...\n argv[2] \u003d \"echo \\\"${TEST_PARENT+set}|${TEST_VAR}\\\" \u003e\u00261\";\n\nthen make sure the output is \"|test\"",
      "parentUuid": "8c4cc136_a3bbfddf",
      "revId": "08e8c229b495d3413ca41a02b345bf19cc151064",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
